<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>title</code> attribute provides advisory text about an element. On desktop browsers, hovering the mouse over the element displays a tooltip after a short delay. This is the <code>title</code> <em>attribute</em> on HTML elements — not the <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> element used in <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> for the page title.</p>
<p><strong>Applies to:</strong> Any HTML element (it is a global attribute)</p>

<h2>Values</h2>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Value</th><th>Behavior</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Any string</td><td>Displayed as a tooltip on mouse hover. Inherited by child elements unless they have their own <code>title</code>.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>""</code> (empty string)</td><td>Explicitly suppresses an inherited tooltip. The element shows no tooltip.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>(not set)</td><td>Inherits the nearest ancestor's <code>title</code> value, if any.</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

